=09
<meta name=3D"DC.Creator" content=3D"Weisstein, Eric W.">
=09
<meta name=3D"DC.Description" content=3D"The adjacency matrix, sometimes al=
so called the connection matrix, of a simple labeled graph is a matrix with=
 rows and columns labeled by graph vertices, with a 1 or 0 in position (v_i=
,v_j) according to whether v_i and v_j are adjacent or not. For a simple gr=
aph with no self-loops, the adjacency matrix must have 0s on the diagonal. =
For an undirected graph, the adjacency matrix is symmetric.  The illustrati=
on above shows adjacency matrices for particular labelings of the claw grap=
h, cycle...">
